# Quick start guide: Insight AnalytiX v2.1.0

Use this guide to deploy the Insight AnalytiX node and initiate your first data discovery scan.

## 1. Prepare the environment
Verify that your server meets these minimum requirements before you begin:
* **Operating system:** RHEL 8.x or Ubuntu 20.04 LTS.
* **Network:** Open ports **443** and **8080**.
* **Permissions:** Root or `sudo` privileges.

## 2. Install the node
Use these commands to download and install the engine. 

```bash
# Download the package
wget [https://downloads.datadynamics.com/insight-analytix-v2.1.tar.gz](https://downloads.datadynamics.com/insight-analytix-v2.1.tar.gz)

# Extract the files and navigate to the directory
tar -xvf insight-analytix-v2.1.tar.gz && cd insight-analytix-v2.1

# Run the installer
sudo ./install.sh --management-ip <YOUR_STORAGE_X_IP>
```
## 3. Verify connectivity
Confirm that the service is running correctly:

```bash
systemctl status analytix-engine
```
The status must display **active (running)**.

## 4. Run your first scan
1. Log in to the **StorageX management console**.

2. Go to **Data Discovery** > **AnalytiX Nodes**.

3. Select your new node and select **Create New Scan**.

4. Define your source path and select **Start**.